# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:66
translate spanish hwb_s37_7a304bc7:

    # "The air seems to crackle with electric anticipation. It’s on people’s faces and in the way that they move, the energy like a wave that flows over them."
    "El aire parece chisporrotear con una anticipación eléctrica. Se ve en los rostros de la gente y en la forma en que se mueven, la energía como una ola que fluye sobre ellos."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:68
translate spanish hwb_s37_04e099c4:

    # "We all share a feeling of excitement and of unity. Every single person here has been waiting for months for this day to arrive."
    "Todos compartimos un sentimiento de emoción y unidad. Cada persona aquí ha estado esperando meses para que llegue este día."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:70
translate spanish hwb_s37_5c9fccf3:

    # "And it’s finally here."
    "Y por fin ha llegado."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:72
translate spanish hwb_s37_ae6d5a88:

    # "High tents and portable stages dominate the space around us. Between those and the trees, and most of all the noise, you’d never guess that there’s a city and highway just a couple miles away."
    "Carpas altas y escenarios portátiles dominan el espacio a nuestro alrededor. Entre ellos y los árboles, y sobre todo el ruido, nunca dirías que hay una ciudad y una autopista a solo un par de kilómetros."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:74
translate spanish hwb_s37_f271944c:

    # "Drum beats and muted chords float by as musicians do a few last-minute soundchecks. They’re barely audible over the sound of thousands of chattering voices."
    "Golpes de tambor y acordes apagados flotan mientras los músicos hacen las últimas pruebas de sonido. Apenas se oyen por encima del sonido de miles de voces parloteando."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:76
translate spanish hwb_s37_c0cd180e:

    # "Folks of all different shapes, sizes and colors mill around us. It’s like social boundaries have been eroded. I think that’s a sentiment Gramps would like."
    "Gente de todas las formas, tamaños y colores deambula a nuestro alrededor. Es como si las barreras sociales se hubieran erosionado. Creo que es un sentimiento que al Abuelo le gustaría."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:93
translate spanish hwb_s37_ee32b9a1:

    # "One girl in the crowd seems to fit right in with her e-cigarette."
    "Una chica entre la multitud parece encajar perfectamente con su cigarrillo electrónico."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:98
translate spanish hwb_s37_8da461c8:

    # "{color=#f5deb3}???" "{font=gui/fonts/SourceHanSans-Regular.otf}黄金は？{/font}"
    "{color=#f5deb3}???\" \"{font=gui/fonts/SourceHanSans-Regular.otf}黄金は？{/font}"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:103
translate spanish hwb_s37_d00a065b:

    # "Or maybe she's from the other side of the world."
    "O tal vez sea del otro lado del mundo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:110
translate spanish hwb_s37_f6332ba4:

    # Marina "Sorry, I don't speak Chinese."
    Marina "Извините, я не говорю по-китайски."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:115
translate spanish hwb_s37_76469cb0:

    # "???" "Gold. Where is it?"
    "Oro. ¿Dónde está?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:120
translate spanish hwb_s37_6f184955:

    # Amber "It's already been found."
    Amber "Его уже нашли."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:124
translate spanish hwb_s37_133b3b3b:

    # "???" "{font=gui/fonts/SourceHanSans-Regular.otf}チェ、めんどう。{/font}"
    "{font=gui/fonts/SourceHanSans-Regular.otf}Che, qué fastidio.{/font}"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:138
translate spanish hwb_s37_197dade5:

    # Amber "What do you think that was about?"
    Amber "Как думаешь, о чем это она?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:142
translate spanish hwb_s37_f4615e2c:

    # Marina "Maybe she's from some futuristic foreign rebellion group that needs the gold to fund their diabolocal schemes?"
    Marina "Может, она из тех самых групп зарубежных бунтовщиков-футуристов, и им нужно золото, чтобы воплотить свои дьявольские планы?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:146
translate spanish hwb_s37_d88b05ea:

    # Amber "I like the idea, but what are the chances of that?"
    Amber "Идея мне нравится, но какой шанс, что это действительно так?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:150
translate spanish hwb_s37_36d63e31:

    # Amber "Still, I could have sworn she was from around here."
    Amber "И все же могу поклясться, что она местная."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:154
translate spanish hwb_s37_bd5c3970:

    # Marina "It's honestly kind of hard to tell."
    Marina "Да вообще-то трудно судить."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:157
translate spanish hwb_s37_5dd94145:

    # "Idly, I use my thumb to trace a heart into Marina’s palm. She squeezes back, probably unaware of what the shape was but understanding all the same."
    "Sin pensar, uso mi pulgar para dibujar un corazón en la palma de Marina. Ella me aprieta la mano de vuelta, probablemente sin saber qué forma hice, pero entendiéndolo igual."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:161
translate spanish hwb_s37_be76771d:

    # Marina "So where do we go now?"
    Marina "Куда пойдем теперь?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:167
translate spanish hwb_s37_b2dedaca:

    # Amber "Now we go stand in line while they check wristbands and let people onto the grounds. It’s gonna be a while."
    Amber "Теперь пойдем стоять в очереди, пока они проверяют браслеты и пускают людей внутрь. Это займет какое-то время."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:171
translate spanish hwb_s37_85c26bf6:

    # Marina "One more traffic jam, huh?"
    Marina "Еще одна пробка, да?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:175
translate spanish hwb_s37_2bb48def:

    # Amber "That’s right. One more."
    Amber "Точно. Еще одна."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:177
translate spanish hwb_s37_daca6e73:

    # "Even if I hadn’t been mapping the grounds in my head, it’d be impossible to get lost. Bored looking staff are positioned every few yards, holding signs with arrows and directions."
    "Incluso si no hubiera estado trazando el terreno en mi cabeza, sería imposible perderse. El personal, con aspecto aburrido, está colocado cada pocos metros, sosteniendo letreros con flechas y direcciones."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:179
translate spanish hwb_s37_c2d098bb:

    # "Like molasses, the throng of people that we’ve joined oozes down the trail. We all hold each other back, the sheer numbers making for slow going."
    "Como melaza, la multitud a la que nos hemos unido avanza lentamente por el sendero. Todos nos frenamos unos a otros, la gran cantidad de gente hace que sea lento."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:181
translate spanish hwb_s37_a7f42931:

    # "Nearly a hundred thousand people attend each year."
    "Casi cien mil personas asisten cada año."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:183
translate spanish hwb_s37_10f96f6f:

    # Marina "What time does the show start?"
    Marina "Во сколько начнется шоу?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:185
translate spanish hwb_s37_829f8a49:

    # Amber "First bands are at like, 11. But the ones we wanna see are later in the evening."
    Amber "Первые группы начнут выступать в 11. Но те, кого мы хотим увидеть, будут позже вечером."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:187
translate spanish hwb_s37_d6848859:

    # Marina "What time is it now?"
    Marina "Который сейчас час?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:189
translate spanish hwb_s37_330960ba:

    # "I use my free hand to shield my eyes as I stare up at the sky."
    "Uso mi mano libre para protegerme los ojos mientras miro al cielo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:193
translate spanish hwb_s37_d68cd26a:

    # Amber "Maybe ten-thirty?"
    Amber "Где-то пол одиннадцатого."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:197
translate spanish hwb_s37_0f178d1d:

    # Marina "You didn’t seriously just use the sun to tell time, did you?"
    Marina "Ты что, серьезно определила время по солнцу?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:201
translate spanish hwb_s37_803924f2:

    # Amber "What, you can’t?"
    Amber "А что, ты не умеешь что ли?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:205
translate spanish hwb_s37_b6175913:

    # Marina "Not all of us were born in the wilderness, Amber."
    Marina "Не все из нас родились в пустошах, Эмбер."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:209
translate spanish hwb_s37_28fa3f36:

    # Amber "Hey, neither was I. Just raised in it."
    Amber "Эй, и я не родилась. Просто выросла там."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:213
translate spanish hwb_s37_29f88e03:

    # Amber "Besides, I checked the time before we got out."
    Amber "И вообще-то я посмотрела время перед тем, как мы ушли."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:217
translate spanish hwb_s37_a5189142:

    # Marina "Okay, that makes more sense."
    Marina "В это больше верится."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:219
translate spanish hwb_s37_aac78939:

    # Amber "I’ll have to show you how to use a sundial sometime, though. It’s pretty handy if you’re ever lost in the woods somewhere."
    Amber "Я научу тебя как-нибудь определять время по солнцу. Это очень удобно, особенно, если ты заблудился где-нибудь в лесу."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:223
translate spanish hwb_s37_41a94c6a:

    # Marina "Right, because knowing the time would definitely be what I’m thinking about then."
    Marina "Ага, как будто время это первое, о чем я буду беспокоиться в такой ситуации."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:227
translate spanish hwb_s37_2bb257bc:

    # Amber "You should be! You’ll wanna know how long before it gets dark and cold so you can find shelter."
    Amber "Как раз таки об этом и следует беспокоиться! Ты ведь наверняка захочешь узнать сколько времени осталось  до наступления холодной ночи, и как быстро тебе нужно найти убежище."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:231
translate spanish hwb_s37_3cfe0d9b:

    # Marina "I’ll just ask you to do that."
    Marina "Я просто спрошу тебя об этом."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:235
translate spanish hwb_s37_83eebd9e:

    # Amber "What if I’m not with you?"
    Amber "А если меня не будет рядом?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:239
translate spanish hwb_s37_860e3c92:

    # Marina "Why wouldn’t you be?"
    Marina "А почему тебя не будет?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:241
translate spanish hwb_s37_4fe604a5:

    # "I kiss her right then and there."
    "La beso ahí mismo, en ese momento."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:243
translate spanish hwb_s37_135fad98:

    # "After the past few days, I was a little worried that things would be awkward. Silences and trailing off sentences."
    "Después de los últimos días, me preocupaba un poco que las cosas fueran incómodas. Silencios y frases que se quedan a medias."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:245
translate spanish hwb_s37_62e33479:

    # "But no, it’s like we never fought; never argued. Like I never blew up at her."
    "Pero no, es como si nunca hubiéramos peleado; nunca discutido. Como si nunca le hubiera explotado."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:247
translate spanish hwb_s37_1c6fff5f:

    # "That might be my favorite thing about Marina. There's a growing list of those."
    "Eso podría ser lo que más me gusta de Marina. La lista de esas cosas sigue creciendo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:249
translate spanish hwb_s37_3cb337b0:

    # "She really thinks I can do no wrong."
    "Ella realmente cree que no puedo hacer nada mal."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:251
translate spanish hwb_s37_e05f5b0b:

    # "I don’t know what I did to deserve her, or even if I do, but I’m pretty dang happy with how it all turned out."
    "No sé qué hice para merecerla, o si siquiera la merezco, pero estoy bastante feliz con cómo resultó todo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:253
translate spanish hwb_s37_2752e996:

    # "The line speeds up once we actually hit the festival entrance and are rushed through the gate."
    "La fila se acelera una vez que llegamos a la entrada del festival y nos apresuran a pasar por la puerta."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:255
translate spanish hwb_s37_ee136632:

    # "A pair of attendants pat us down. Since we’re not carrying any drugs or weapons, we’re waved on through."
    "Un par de asistentes nos registran. Como no llevamos drogas ni armas, nos dejan pasar."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:257
translate spanish hwb_s37_be6835c6:

    # "Passing underneath a broad opening display, we’ve officially arrived."
    "Al pasar bajo una gran exhibición de entrada, hemos llegado oficialmente."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:259
translate spanish hwb_s37_c9b40461:

    # "Marina spins towards me, bouncing on her heels."
    "Marina gira hacia mí, saltando sobre sus talones."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:261
translate spanish hwb_s37_7736d5a8:

    # Marina "We made it!"
    Marina "Мы это сделали!"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:263
translate spanish hwb_s37_f4d5cb78:

    # Amber "Hell yeah we did."
    Amber "Да, черт возьми, мы сделали это."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:265
translate spanish hwb_s37_ecdd289a:

    # "It’s been a long journey. I think of everything we’ve done and all the places we’ve been. The people we’ve met."
    "Ha sido un largo viaje. Pienso en todo lo que hemos hecho y todos los lugares donde hemos estado. La gente que hemos conocido."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:267
translate spanish hwb_s37_4a162947:

    # "And how all of those led us to this."
    "Y cómo todo eso nos llevó hasta aquí."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:269
translate spanish hwb_s37_4d386fdf:

    # "I smile as I reach for her hand yet again. Meeting it halfway, since she went for mine, too."
    "Sonrío mientras busco su mano una vez más. Encuentro la suya a medio camino, porque ella también buscó la mía."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:273
translate spanish hwb_s37_16a26e87:

    # Amber "Food?"
    Amber "Проголодалась? "

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:277
translate spanish hwb_s37_6ddf479c:

    # Marina "Foooood."
    Marina "О даааааа."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:279
translate spanish hwb_s37_d22f70f0:

    # "I haven’t had a good meal in… Over a day, now that I think about it."
    "No he tenido una buena comida en... Más de un día, ahora que lo pienso."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:283
translate spanish hwb_s37_58eb4b78:

    # "And once I do, I can’t {i}stop{/i} thinking about it."
    "Y una vez que lo hago, no puedo {i}dejar{/i} de pensar en ello."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:287
translate spanish hwb_s37_17bb066b:

    # "I lead the way to the \"food court,\" which is just a bunch of trucks and tents arranged in an aisle."
    "Guío el camino hacia la \"plaza de comidas\", que no es más que un montón de camiones y carpas dispuestos en un pasillo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:289
translate spanish hwb_s37_f15bd937:

    # "Everything for sale is greasy but delicious. It’s the kind of food that’ll stop your heart but heal your soul."
    "Todo lo que venden es grasoso pero delicioso. Es el tipo de comida que te para el corazón pero te cura el alma."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:291
translate spanish hwb_s37_9e64ced5:

    # "We pause at the closest truck to us to read the menu."
    "Nos detenemos en el camión más cercano para leer el menú."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:295
translate spanish hwb_s37_a13e128c:

    # Marina "Amber."
    Marina "Эмбер."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:299
translate spanish hwb_s37_6660f616:

    # Amber "Marina."
    Amber "Марина."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:303
translate spanish hwb_s37_920a15a0:

    # Marina "Is that like… a typo or something? It says they have deep-fried candy bars."
    Marina "Это… опечатка или что? Тут сказано, что у них есть жаренные шоколадные батончики."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:307
translate spanish hwb_s37_086a2a23:

    # Amber "Nah, those are really popular at fairs and festivals."
    Amber "Нет, они очень популярны на различных ярмарках и фестивалях."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:309
translate spanish hwb_s37_bb870ee1:

    # "She gives me that \"I know you’re making this up\" look that she’s perfected."
    "Me lanza esa mirada de \"sé que te lo estás inventando\" que ha perfeccionado."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:313
translate spanish hwb_s37_35e2ade6:

    # Marina "Yeah, right."
    Marina "Ага, конечно."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:321
translate spanish hwb_s37_37108f4c:

    # Amber "No, I’m actually dead serious. Candy bars, pickles, people… You can get almost anything deep fried at places like this."
    Amber "Нет, я серьезно. Шоколадные батончики, соленья, люди… В таких местах как это, отжарить можно все, что угодно."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:325
translate spanish hwb_s37_6e752a7d:

    # Amber "One guy I met figured out how to deep fry the concept of objective truth."
    Amber "Я встретила одного парня, который знал, как отжарить концепт абсолютной истины."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:329
translate spanish hwb_s37_3aae9c6c:

    # Marina "What was that like?"
    Marina "И как же?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:333
translate spanish hwb_s37_719aadf5:

    # Amber "Technically unknowable depending on who you talk to."
    Amber "Технически никак, но вообще зависит от того, как далеко зайдет обсуждение."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:341
translate spanish hwb_s37_7818710f:

    # Amber "No, I’m actually dead serious. Candy bars, pickles, snack cakes… You can get almost anything deep fried at places like this."
    Amber "Нет, я серьезно. Шоколадные батончики, соленья, пирожные… В таких местах как это, ты можешь найти что угодно прожаренное во фиритюре."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:345
translate spanish hwb_s37_124de433:

    # Marina "Ever had one?"
    Marina "Ты пробовала когда-нибудь?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:347
translate spanish hwb_s37_d04dd517:

    # Amber "No way. That’s too much, even for me."
    Amber "Нет, это слишком. Даже для меня."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:351
translate spanish hwb_s37_9f5a454c:

    # "The thought alone makes me kind of queasy. So much grease."
    "Solo de pensarlo me da un poco de náuseas. Tanta grasa."


translate spanish strings:
    old "Cook"
    new "Повар"
# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:353
translate spanish hwb_s37_db0d73d9:

    # "Cook" "Order up!"
    Cook "Заказывайте!"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:355
translate spanish hwb_s37_923ef9d4:

    # "To highlight my point, the guy running the fryer pulls out a crispy looking… blob. It’s impossible to tell what it is because of the batter."
    "Para reforzar mi punto, el tipo que maneja la freidora saca un bulto crujiente... imposible de identificar por el rebozado."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:357
translate spanish hwb_s37_18bb0afd:

    # "After wiping off some of the oil - which doesn’t seem to change much - he wraps it in wax paper and hands it to the person waiting by the window."
    "Después de limpiar un poco el aceite —que no parece cambiar mucho—, lo envuelve en papel encerado y se lo entrega a la persona que espera junto a la ventanilla."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:359
translate spanish hwb_s37_0c6ac489:

    # "He bites into it with a look of pleasure, though I still can’t tell what he’s eating."
    "Le da un mordisco con una expresión de placer, aunque aún no puedo distinguir qué está comiendo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:361
translate spanish hwb_s37_f9e57a50:

    # Amber "Want something?"
    Amber "Хочешь что-нибудь?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:365
translate spanish hwb_s37_94c00816:

    # "Vaguely green, Marina shakes her head."
    "Marina, ligeramente pálida, niega con la cabeza."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:367
translate spanish hwb_s37_0d974bd8:

    # Marina "Pass."
    Marina "Я пас."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:371
translate spanish hwb_s37_283ba570:

    # "Not much further down the line, we find a regular pizza stand and order a couple slices."
    "Un poco más adelante, encontramos un puesto de pizza normal y pedimos un par de rebanadas."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:373
translate spanish hwb_s37_e1820cf0:

    # "We stand a little out of the way while we eat, trying to keep the toppings from all sliding onto our rapidly deteriorating plates."
    "Nos paramos un poco apartadas mientras comemos, tratando de evitar que los ingredientes se resbalen en nuestros platos que se deshacen rápidamente."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:375
translate spanish hwb_s37_3f0fb71b:

    # "When we’re done, I drag a napkin across my face. It comes away orange with grease."
    "Cuando terminamos, paso una servilleta por mi cara. Sale anaranjada de grasa."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:379
translate spanish hwb_s37_528b1bea:

    # Marina "Missed a spot."
    Marina "Пропустила пятнышко."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:381
translate spanish hwb_s37_1ce7a8dc:

    # "She leans over and wipes dry a spot above my upper lip, then kisses it."
    "Se inclina y me limpia un punto sobre mi labio superior, luego lo besa."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:385
translate spanish hwb_s37_68e6b293:

    # Amber "Wait, wait, show me where, again."
    Amber "Подожди, подожди, покажи еще разок, где там пятнышко."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:387
translate spanish hwb_s37_2b9425d9:

    # "This time she doesn’t dab before leaning in to kiss me. I can taste the pizza on her breath. Or maybe it’s mine."
    "Esta vez no se limpia antes de inclinarse para besarme. Puedo sentir el sabor de la pizza en su aliento. O tal vez sea el mío."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:391
translate spanish hwb_s37_025abfc1:

    # "When we part again, we’re both smiling."
    "Cuando nos separamos de nuevo, ambas estamos sonriendo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:397
translate spanish hwb_s37_1f8f2e4b:

    # Marina "You should check the sun. What time is it?"
    Marina "Взгляни на солнце. Который час?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:401
translate spanish hwb_s37_f1f21bf6:

    # "I make a big show of looking up at the sky, then back down, and pretending to think hard."
    "Hago una gran escena mirando al cielo, luego hacia abajo, y finjo pensar intensamente."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:407
translate spanish hwb_s37_4001a1de:

    # Amber "I’d say it’s time for us to get a watch."
    Amber "Скажем так, настало время купить часы."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:411
translate spanish hwb_s37_af980656:

    # Marina "That is literally a joke that my dad makes. His dad probably said it, and it was probably old then. No. Just no."
    Marina "Эту шутку как раз любит мой отец. Его отец, вероятно, рассказал ее ему, и уже тогда она была стара как мир."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:415
translate spanish hwb_s37_7d3c9ff6:

    # Amber "Ouch, tough crowd. I’m hurt."
    Amber "Эй, как грубо. Задела за живое."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:419
translate spanish hwb_s37_0975704e:

    # Amber "Really though, it’s probably a little bit past noon. We’ve still got a long time."
    Amber "Ну а если серьезно, то сейчас лишь немного за 12 . У нас еще много времени."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:423
translate spanish hwb_s37_bb2f2780:

    # Marina "Wanna go check out some of the other bands?"
    Marina "Хочешь пойти посмотреть на другие группы?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:427
translate spanish hwb_s37_e5bf5a31:

    # Amber "Yeah, sure."
    Amber "Конечно."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:429
translate spanish hwb_s37_12f1a2a2:

    # "I pull out the schedule that we got by the entrance and pass it to her."
    "Saco el horario que conseguimos en la entrada y se lo paso."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:433
translate spanish hwb_s37_ad99151c:

    # Amber "I don’t really know any of these groups. Lemme know if there’s someone you wanna see."
    Amber "Я никогда не слышала про эти группы. Дай знать, есть ли тут кто-нибудь, кого бы ты хотела послушать."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:437
translate spanish hwb_s37_d04eb883:

    # "Marina skims over the list of names before she squeals."
    "Marina hojea la lista de nombres antes de soltar un chillido."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:441
translate spanish hwb_s37_24385c77:

    # Marina "Oh my God! Yes! Them, I wanna see them!"
    Marina "Боже мой! Да! Это они, я хочу их увидеть!"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:443
translate spanish hwb_s37_e5f6adfb:

    # "She points out someone who’s about to set up on the main stage."
    "Señala a alguien que está a punto de instalarse en el escenario principal."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:447
translate spanish hwb_s37_7c96e94a:

    # Amber "Alright, that should be this way."
    Amber "Хорошо, нам сюда."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:449
translate spanish hwb_s37_3d15f4c4:

    # "Literally bouncing with excitement, I lead her through the crowds."
    "Literalmente saltando de emoción, la guío entre la multitud."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:453
translate spanish hwb_s37_9de13b50:

    # Amber "What kind of music are they?"
    Amber "В каком жанре они играют?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:455
translate spanish hwb_s37_4d7fbad6:

    # "I have to shout now, because the music is much louder over here. Marina presses close to me to respond."
    "Tengo que gritar ahora, porque la música es mucho más fuerte aquí. Marina se acerca a mí para responder."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:459
translate spanish hwb_s37_f155c636:

    # Marina "They’re rappers. Two of them. Their new album got super popular. And like, they’re even doing this version of it where all the instruments are cats."
    Marina "Они оба рэперы. Их новый альбом стал мега популярным. Они даже делают версию, где все их инструменты заменят на котиков."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:463
translate spanish hwb_s37_fb45a72f:

    # Amber "...Right."
    Amber "...Ясно."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:465
translate spanish hwb_s37_c89e863b:

    # "I’m not really into rap, but whatever. It’s not like we’ve got anywhere else to be yet. And I’m pretty sure Marina still isn’t super into weird old people jam bands."
    "No soy muy fan del rap, pero da igual. No es como si tuviéramos otro lugar donde estar aún. Y estoy bastante segura de que Marina tampoco es muy fan de las bandas de viejos raros."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:469
translate spanish hwb_s37_c4944378:

    # "We get to the stage right as a set ends. Because there are a lot of people leaving, it’s a bit like swimming upstream. But we manage to make it close to the stage."
    "Llegamos al escenario justo cuando termina una presentación. Como hay mucha gente saliendo, es un poco como nadar contra corriente. Pero logramos acercarnos al escenario."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:473
translate spanish hwb_s37_d6098971:

    # Amber "How are you liking it so far?"
    Amber "Ну что, нравится?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:477
translate spanish hwb_s37_4df557f6:

    # Marina "Which part?"
    Marina "Что именно?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:479
translate spanish hwb_s37_8ac6d503:

    # Amber "All of it!"
    Amber "Все это!"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:483
translate spanish hwb_s37_bde4b812:

    # Marina "It’s kinda crazy. But it’s fun! I like seeing all the different people."
    Marina "Это безумно, но так весело! Мне нравится быть среди всех этих настолько разных людей."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:487
translate spanish hwb_s37_6ad03727:

    # Amber "Yeah, you get all types."
    Amber "Да, разнообразия здесь хватает."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:489
translate spanish hwb_s37_a465b5fa:

    # "Bass booms from a speaker close to us. It’s just playing a pre-recorded medley, but Marina sings along to a few of the songs."
    "El bajo retumba desde un altavoz cercano. Solo están reproduciendo un popurrí pregrabado, pero Marina canta algunas canciones."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:491
translate spanish hwb_s37_09acc8ee:

    # "A little while later, the two rappers come out on stage and everyone cheers. I turn around, surprised at how big the crowd’s gotten again."
    "Poco después, los dos raperos salen al escenario y todos vitorean. Me giro, sorprendida de lo grande que se ha vuelto la multitud otra vez."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:495
translate spanish hwb_s37_be9ad5b1:

    # "When I look back at Marina, she’s not paying any attention to me, just grinning up at the stage."
    "Cuando miro de nuevo a Marina, no me presta atención, solo sonríe mirando al escenario."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:499
translate spanish hwb_s37_1f591370:

    # "Forty minutes later, the pair leaves the stage to thunderous applause and cheers. Even I clap for them - they were pretty good."
    "Cuarenta minutos después, la pareja abandona el escenario entre aplausos y vítores atronadores. Hasta yo aplaudo — estuvieron bastante bien."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:501
translate spanish hwb_s37_5f352093:

    # Amber "How’d you like it?"
    Amber "Ну как, понравилось?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:505
translate spanish hwb_s37_5d0c61f4:

    # Marina "They were so good! So good!"
    Marina "Они были так хороши! Так хороши!"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:507
translate spanish hwb_s37_e049ee12:

    # Marina "Like whoa. If I’d known they were playing today I’d have been even more excited for this. They’re one of my favorite bands in the world."
    Marina "Просто бомба! Если бы я знала, что они будут выступать сегодня, я бы еще больше ждала этого дня. Они одна из моих самых любимых групп в мире."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:509
translate spanish hwb_s37_5fe9a1fb:

    # Amber "Did you just not look at the lineup or something?"
    Amber "А ты что, не смотрела список выступающих?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:513
translate spanish hwb_s37_6b1b93f0:

    # Marina "I guess not. I kind of thought all the bands would be like what you listen to."
    Marina "Нет. Я думала, что все выступающие сегодня группы будут в стиле, который любишь ты."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:517
translate spanish hwb_s37_914604c3:

    # "I burst out laughing."
    "Me echo a reír."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:521
translate spanish hwb_s37_2252080c:

    # Amber "I don’t think they could sell out a festival like that. Not to this many people at least."
    Amber "Я не думаю, что они смогли бы организовать такой фестиваль. По крайней мере, здесь не было бы столько народу."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:523
translate spanish hwb_s37_ae3ae72b:

    # Amber "But it’s fine. I like getting to hear new stuff, too."
    Amber "Но все в порядке. Я тоже люблю послушать что-нибудь новое."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:547
translate spanish hwb_s37_363e00c9:

    # "That’s how we spend the next few hours: going from stage to stage to watch bands I’ve never heard of. Sometimes they’re groups Marina likes, and sometimes they just have a weird name."
    "Así pasamos las siguientes horas: yendo de escenario en escenario para ver bandas que nunca había escuchado. A veces son grupos que le gustan a Marina, y otras solo tienen un nombre raro."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:553
translate spanish hwb_s37_46e56baf:

    # "Around the time the sun starts to go down, we head back to the east stage where we’ll see our last show of the day."
    "Cerca de la hora en que el sol comienza a ocultarse, regresamos al escenario este, donde veremos nuestro último show del día."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:555
translate spanish hwb_s37_376970df:

    # "Marina’s in the lead this time. We’ve gone between the stages so many times that we have a good feel for how to get around."
    "Esta vez Marina va al frente. Hemos ido y venido entre los escenarios tantas veces que ya tenemos una buena idea de cómo movernos."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:557
translate spanish hwb_s37_7c69f266:

    # "We find a spot on a little grassy slope and sit down."
    "Encontramos un lugar en una pequeña pendiente cubierta de hierba y nos sentamos."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:561
translate spanish hwb_s37_ee2d26ca:

    # Marina "Are you sure? Won’t it be hard to see?"
    Marina "Ты уверена? Отсюда будет хорошо видно?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:565
translate spanish hwb_s37_416c4d79:

    # Amber "Nah, we’ve got a good view from here. And it seems like it’ll be a small crowd."
    Amber "Ага, отсюда открывается прекрасный обзор. И, кажется, здесь не будет особо большой толпы."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:567
translate spanish hwb_s37_ca8f767f:

    # "Of course, \"small\" still means thousands of people here. It’s just small compared to some of the other acts."
    "Por supuesto, \"pequeño\" aquí sigue significando miles de personas. Solo es pequeño en comparación con otros actos."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:569
translate spanish hwb_s37_d7806505:

    # "Marina bumps my shoulder."
    "Marina me da un codazo en el hombro."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:573
translate spanish hwb_s37_1af3a9ab:

    # Marina "Excited?"
    Marina "Волнуешься?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:577
translate spanish hwb_s37_c3480bdc:

    # Amber "Bit of an understatement."
    Amber "Не особо."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:579
translate spanish hwb_s37_12cf79ff:

    # "Up on stage, there are banners and a giant cloth backdrop that hang from a bar. They’re decorated with a familiar black logo that I could draw in my sleep."
    "En el escenario, hay pancartas y un telón de tela gigante que cuelgan de una barra. Están decorados con un logotipo negro familiar que podría dibujar dormido."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:581
translate spanish hwb_s37_c7e325bb:

    # "The breeze causes it to shake and sway, like it’s as excited as I am."
    "La brisa hace que se agite y se balancee, como si estuviera tan emocionado como yo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:583
translate spanish hwb_s37_f40d2727:

    # "We’re pretty severe outliers when it comes to the average age of this crowd. The rows of people in front of us are represented by a smattering of bald spots and bandanas."
    "Somos casos atípicos bastante severos en cuanto a la edad promedio de esta multitud. Las filas de personas frente a nosotros están representadas por un puñado de calvas y pañuelos."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:585
translate spanish hwb_s37_6db95d03:

    # "I’m about to make a joke of it to Marina, when the band comes on-stage and any words are lost in the deafening roar of applause."
    "Estoy a punto de hacerle un chiste a Marina, cuando la banda sale al escenario y cualquier palabra se pierde en el ensordecedor rugido de aplausos."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:589
translate spanish hwb_s37_6201a7aa:

    # "Beside me, Marina’s voice joins the thousands whooping and yelling."
    "A mi lado, la voz de Marina se une a los miles que gritan y vociferan."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:591
translate spanish hwb_s37_03737d6b:

    # "Usually, I’m way too self-conscious for this sort of thing, but what the hell? I cheer too."
    "Normalmente, soy demasiado consciente de mí misma para este tipo de cosas, pero ¿qué demonios? Yo también animo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:593
translate spanish hwb_s37_e76686ff:

    # "With just a wave and not a word of introduction, they launch into the first song. It was the opening track on their second album, back from before I was born."
    "Con solo una onda y sin una palabra de presentación, arrancan con la primera canción. Era la pista de apertura de su segundo álbum, de antes de que yo naciera."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:595
translate spanish hwb_s37_bad64275:

    # "They’ve been playing this one longer than I’ve been alive."
    "Han estado tocando esta canción más tiempo del que he estado viva."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:597
translate spanish hwb_s37_356ba0a8:

    # "It’s a great song, though. They’re all great songs."
    "Es una gran canción, eso sí. Todas son grandes canciones."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:599
translate spanish hwb_s37_55010498:

    # "The whole set is magical. They go from one song to another without stopping in-between. If you didn’t know the music, you’d probably think it was all just one, super long track."
    "Todo el set es mágico. Pasan de una canción a otra sin detenerse entre medio. Si no conocieras la música, probablemente pensarías que es una sola pista súper larga."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:601
translate spanish hwb_s37_01c497f6:

    # "Even though it spans a few decades’ worth of albums, everything flows seamlessly, like it was meant to be heard this way."
    "Aunque abarca álbumes de varias décadas, todo fluye sin problemas, como si estuviera hecho para escucharse así."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:605
translate spanish hwb_s37_4545b94a:

    # "At some point I close my eyes, though I don’t notice myself doing it. I’m lost, but in the good way. With Marina beside me, gently swaying."
    "En algún momento cierro los ojos, aunque no me doy cuenta de que lo hago. Estoy perdida, pero de la buena manera. Con Marina a mi lado, balanceándose suavemente."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:607
translate spanish hwb_s37_2fb890bd:

    # "There’s not a single sad thought in my head."
    "No hay ni un solo pensamiento triste en mi cabeza."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:609
translate spanish hwb_s37_f5671b9c:

    # "For forty minutes, everything in the world seems right."
    "Durante cuarenta minutos, todo en el mundo parece estar bien."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:611
translate spanish hwb_s37_0abc0e7c:

    # "I marvel at the odds. That my life could turn around entirely in such a short amount of time."
    "Me maravillo de las probabilidades. Que mi vida pudiera dar un giro completo en tan poco tiempo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:613
translate spanish hwb_s37_8c0cd66d:

    # "Countless cups of coffee and gas station snack packs. Three boxes of gold. Five states. Three weeks of dusty, desert roads. That’s what it took to get us here."
    "Innumerables tazas de café y paquetes de bocadillos de gasolinera. Tres cajas de oro. Cinco estados. Tres semanas de caminos polvorientos en el desierto. Eso es lo que nos llevó hasta aquí."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:615
translate spanish hwb_s37_96aa0277:

    # "All that, and one faulty fuel gauge."
    "Todo eso, y un indicador de combustible defectuoso."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:622
translate spanish hwb_s37_e454b60a:

    # "I open my eyes and look at Marina."
    "Abro los ojos y miro a Marina."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:624
translate spanish hwb_s37_e5d20c4c:

    # "To my surprise, she’s looking right back at me."
    "Para mi sorpresa, ella me está devolviendo la mirada."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:629
translate spanish hwb_s37_8a58c011:

    # "She scoots a little bit closer and leans against me, her head on my shoulder. I put my head on hers, and together we rock in time to the music."
    "Se acerca un poco más y se recuesta contra mí, apoyando su cabeza en mi hombro. Pongo mi cabeza sobre la suya, y juntas nos mecemos al ritmo de la música."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:631
translate spanish hwb_s37_7442dfc2:

    # "Then it stops. Everyone cheers again."
    "Luego se detiene. Todos vitorean de nuevo."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:633
translate spanish hwb_s37_3dff53a1:

    # "And the frontman holds up a finger. It’s the first break there’s been in the whole set."
    "Y el vocalista levanta un dedo. Es la primera pausa que ha habido en todo el set."

translate spanish strings:
    old "Frontman"
    new "Солист"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:635
translate spanish hwb_s37_9057857a:

    # "Frontman" "One more song."
    Frontman "Еще одна песня."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:641
translate spanish hwb_s37_6444fa40:

    # "Then he plays those guitar strums I had come to know so well, the ones that I was both dreading and looking forward to the most. It’s the most familiar intro in the world to me, and of course it’s their swan song."
    "Luego toca esos rasgueos de guitarra que había llegado a conocer tan bien, los que más temía y anhelaba a la vez. Es la introducción más familiar del mundo para mí, y por supuesto es su canto del cisne."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:645
translate spanish hwb_s37_7066fe67:

    # "Gramps’ and my favorite."
    "La favorita del abuelo y mía."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:649
translate spanish hwb_s37_210c01c8:

    # "I can feel Marina’s worried gaze, wondering like always if I’m about to break down and cry."
    "Puedo sentir la mirada preocupada de Marina, preguntándose como siempre si estoy a punto de derrumbarme y llorar."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:653
translate spanish hwb_s37_37742db6:

    # "But this time I meet her look, and I smile as I press my lips against hers."
    "Pero esta vez encuentro su mirada, y sonrío mientras presiono mis labios contra los suyos."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:655
translate spanish hwb_s37_ccbf4bfb:

    # "I’m with the girl I love, seeing my favorite band live, as they perform my favorite song. What’s not to smile about?"
    "Estoy con la chica que amo, viendo a mi banda favorita en vivo, mientras tocan mi canción favorita. ¿De qué no sonreír?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:657
translate spanish hwb_s37_cbe5af37:

    # "Somewhere, I hope that Gramps is smiling too. If there’s an afterlife, I hope they get free tickets to the festival."
    "En algún lugar, espero que el abuelo también esté sonriendo. Si hay un más allá, espero que consigan boletos gratis para el festival."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:661
translate spanish hwb_s37_965a1a41:

    # "A single, bittersweet tear leaks out of my eye, rolling down my face and onto our lips."
    "Una sola lágrima agridulce se escapa de mi ojo, rodando por mi rostro y cayendo en nuestros labios."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:663
translate spanish hwb_s37_0e5058ba:

    # "I picture Gramps here beside me, not replacing Marina but with us. I know he would’ve liked her."
    "Imagino al abuelo aquí a mi lado, no reemplazando a Marina sino con nosotras. Sé que le habría gustado."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:665
translate spanish hwb_s37_8dda03be:

    # "As the song comes to an end, I mouth just one word."
    "Cuando la canción llega a su fin, pronuncio en silencio una sola palabra."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:667
translate spanish hwb_s37_983ffc18:

    # "\"Goodbye.\""
    "\"Adiós.\""

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:713
translate spanish hwb_s37_43c3e113:

    # "And then it’s over. I feel something change; not a physical motion but an emotional one. Something new; something deep inside me feels… right."
    "Y entonces termina. Siento algo cambiar; no un movimiento físico sino uno emocional. Algo nuevo; algo profundo dentro de mí se siente... bien."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:715
translate spanish hwb_s37_d1556931:

    # "The band bows. People are screaming their affections. It’s over. We saw them. They performed. It’s over."
    "La banda hace una reverencia. La gente grita su afecto. Se acabó. Las vimos. Tocaron. Se acabó."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:717
translate spanish hwb_s37_d3d954fb:

    # "Beside me, Marina shifts to look to me with a coy look on her face."
    "A mi lado, Marina se mueve para mirarme con una expresión pícara en su rostro."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:741
translate spanish hwb_s37_252ed066:

    # Marina "Amber?"
    Marina "Эмбер?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:743
translate spanish hwb_s37_343b94ea:

    # Amber "Yeah?"
    Amber "Да?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:745
translate spanish hwb_s37_5afc86d0:

    # Marina "I think… I think I know what I want to do with the treasure now."
    Marina "Я думаю… Я думаю что знаю, что хочу сделать с сокровищем."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:748
translate spanish hwb_s37_196c8d75:

    # Amber "Buy cell phones?"
    Amber "Купить смартфон?"

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:767
translate spanish hwb_s37_a7be12af:

    # Marina "No, that would make too much sense."
    Marina "Нет, это слишком практично."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:770
translate spanish hwb_s37_9efcae83:

    # "We both lean in, for once knowing exactly what the other was thinking."
    "Ambas nos inclinamos, por una vez sabiendo exactamente lo que la otra estaba pensando."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:790
translate spanish hwb_s37_8b133a5b:

    # Amber "Yeah, let's just keep doing this instead."
    Amber "Да, давай просто продолжим делать это."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:793
translate spanish hwb_s37_69fa6ddb:

    # Amber "I think I do too."
    Amber "Я думаю, я тоже знаю."

# game/script/hwb_s37.rpy:795
translate spanish hwb_s37_1a69d730:

    # Amber "So where to next?"
    Amber "Ну что, куда дальше?"

